moves.name: Fake Out
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to make the target flinch. Fails unless it is the user's first turn on the field.
moves.shortDesc: Hits first. First turn out only. 100% flinch chance.

moves.name: Psychic
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Parting Shot
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage. If this move is successful, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if the target's Attack and Special Attack stat stages were both unchanged, or if there are no unfainted party members.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers target's Atk, Sp. Atk by 1. User switches.

moves.name: Sludge Wave
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to poison the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to poison adjacent Pokemon.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Shadow Ball
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Psychic Noise
moves.desc: For 2 turns, the target is prevented from restoring any HP as long as it remains active. During the effect, healing and draining moves are unusable, and Abilities and items that grant healing will not heal the user. If an affected Pokemon uses Baton Pass, the replacement will remain unable to restore its HP. Pain Split and the Regenerator Ability are unaffected.
moves.shortDesc: For 2 turns, the target is prevented from healing.

moves.name: Taunt
moves.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokemon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
moves.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

moves.name: Acid Spray
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: U-turn
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
moves.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

moves.name: Trick
moves.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Z-Crystal, if neither is holding an item, if the user is trying to give or take a Mega Stone to or from the species that can Mega Evolve with it, or if the user is trying to give or take a Blue Orb, a Red Orb, a Griseous Orb, a Plate, a Drive, or a Memory to or from a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, or a Silvally, respectively. The target is immune to this move if it has the Sticky Hold Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

moves.name: Venoshock
moves.desc: Power doubles if the target is poisoned.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if the target is poisoned.

moves.name: Clear Smog
moves.desc: Resets all of the target's stat stages to 0.
moves.shortDesc: Resets all of the target's stat stages to 0.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Psyshock
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target based on its Defense instead of Special Defense.
moves.shortDesc: Damages target based on Defense, not Sp. Def.

moves.name: Stored Power
moves.desc: Power is equal to 20+(X*20), where X is the user's total stat stage changes that are greater than 0.
moves.shortDesc: + 20 power for each of the user's stat boosts.

moves.name: Baton Pass
moves.desc: The user is replaced with another Pokemon in its party. The selected Pokemon has the user's stat stage changes, confusion, and certain move effects transferred to it.
moves.shortDesc: User switches, passing stat changes and more.

moves.name: Hyper Beam
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

moves.name: Helping Hand
moves.desc: The power of the target's attack this turn is multiplied by 1.5 (this effect is stackable). Fails if there is no ally adjacent to the user or if the ally already moved this turn, but does not fail if the ally is using a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: One adjacent ally's move power is 1.5x this turn.

moves.name: Fling
moves.desc: The power of this move is based on the user's held item. The held item is lost and it activates for the target if applicable. If there is no target or the target avoids this move by protecting itself, the user's held item is still lost. The user can regain a thrown item with Recycle or the Harvest Ability. Fails if the user has no held item, if the held item cannot be thrown, if the user is under the effect of Embargo or Magic Room, or if the user has the Klutz Ability.
moves.shortDesc: Flings the user's item at the target. Power varies.

moves.name: Future Sight
moves.desc: Deals damage two turns after this move is used. At the end of that turn, the damage is calculated at that time and dealt to the Pokemon at the position the target had when the move was used. If the user is no longer active at the time, damage is calculated based on the user's natural Special Attack stat, types, and level, with no boosts from its held item or Ability. Fails if this move or Doom Desire is already in effect for the target's position.
moves.shortDesc: Hits two turns after being used.

moves.name: Focus Blast
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Psych Up
moves.desc: The user copies all of the target's current stat stage changes.
moves.shortDesc: Copies the target's current stat stages.

moves.name: Calm Mind
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack and Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk and Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Hex
moves.desc: Power doubles if the target has a non-volatile status condition.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if the target has a status ailment.

moves.name: Swift
moves.desc: This move does not check accuracy.
moves.shortDesc: This move does not check accuracy. Hits foes.

moves.name: Poison Jab
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to poison the target.

moves.name: Poltergeist
moves.desc: Fails if the target has no held item.
moves.shortDesc: Fails if the target has no held item.

moves.name: Psychic Terrain
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the terrain becomes Psychic Terrain. During the effect, the power of Psychic-type attacks made by grounded Pokemon is multiplied by 1.3 and grounded Pokemon cannot be hit by moves with priority greater than 0, unless the target is an ally. Camouflage transforms the user into a Psychic type, Nature Power becomes Psychic, and Secret Power has a 30% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage. Fails if the current terrain is Psychic Terrain.
moves.shortDesc: 5 turns. Grounded: +Psychic power, priority-safe.

moves.name: Psybeam
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to confuse the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to confuse the target.

moves.name: Imprison
moves.desc: The user prevents all opposing Pokemon from using any moves that the user also knows as long as the user remains active.
moves.shortDesc: No foe can use any move known by the user.

moves.name: Toxic
moves.desc: Badly poisons the target. If a Poison-type Pokemon uses this move, the target cannot avoid the attack, even if the target is in the middle of a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: Badly poisons the target. Poison types can't miss.

moves.name: Grass Knot
moves.desc: This move's power is 20 if the target weighs less than 10 kg, 40 if less than 25 kg, 60 if less than 50 kg, 80 if less than 100 kg, 100 if less than 200 kg, and 120 if greater than or equal to 200 kg.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the target.

moves.name: Night Shade
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to the user's level.
moves.shortDesc: Does damage equal to the user's level.

moves.name: Uproar
moves.desc: The user spends three turns locked into this move. This move targets an opponent at random on each turn. On the first of the three turns, all sleeping active Pokemon wake up. During the three turns, no active Pokemon can fall asleep by any means, and Pokemon switched in during the effect do not wake up. If the user is prevented from moving or the attack is not successful against the target during one of the turns, the effect ends.
moves.shortDesc: Lasts 3 turns. Active Pokemon cannot fall asleep.

moves.name: Mud-Slap
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's accuracy by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's accuracy by 1.

moves.name: Gunk Shot
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to poison the target.

moves.name: Light Screen
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from special attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Flatter
moves.desc: Raises the target's Special Attack by 1 stage and confuses it.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the target's Sp. Atk by 1 and confuses it.

moves.name: Metronome
moves.desc: A random move is selected for use, other than After You, Apple Acid, Armor Cannon, Assist, Astral Barrage, Aura Wheel, Baneful Bunker, Beak Blast, Behemoth Bash, Behemoth Blade, Belch, Bestow, Blazing Torque, Body Press, Branch Poke, Breaking Swipe, Celebrate, Chatter, Chilling Water, Chilly Reception, Clangorous Soul, Collision Course, Combat Torque, Comeuppance, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Crafty Shield, Decorate, Destiny Bond, Detect, Diamond Storm, Doodle, Double Iron Bash, Double Shock, Dragon Ascent, Dragon Energy, Drum Beating, Dynamax Cannon, Electro Drift, Endure, Eternabeam, False Surrender, Feint, Fiery Wrath, Fillet Away, Fleur Cannon, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Freeze Shock, Freezing Glare, Glacial Lance, Grav Apple, Helping Hand, Hold Hands, Hyper Drill, Hyperspace Fury, Hyperspace Hole, Ice Burn, Instruct, Jet Punch, Jungle Healing, King's Shield, Life Dew, Light of Ruin, Magical Torque, Make It Rain, Mat Block, Me First, Meteor Assault, Metronome, Mimic, Mind Blown, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Moongeist Beam, Nature Power, Nature's Madness, Noxious Torque, Obstruct, Order Up, Origin Pulse, Overdrive, Photon Geyser, Plasma Fists, Population Bomb, Pounce, Power Shift, Precipice Blades, Protect, Pyro Ball, Quash, Quick Guard, Rage Fist, Rage Powder, Raging Bull, Raging Fury, Relic Song, Revival Blessing, Ruination, Salt Cure, Secret Sword, Shed Tail, Shell Trap, Silk Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snap Trap, Snarl, Snatch, Snore, Snowscape, Spectral Thief, Spicy Extract, Spiky Shield, Spirit Break, Spotlight, Springtide Storm, Steam Eruption, Steel Beam, Strange Steam, Struggle, Sunsteel Strike, Surging Strikes, Switcheroo, Techno Blast, Tera Starstorm, Thief, Thousand Arrows, Thousand Waves, Thunder Cage, Thunderous Kick, Tidy Up, Trailblaze, Transform, Trick, Twin Beam, V-create, Wicked Blow, Wicked Torque, or Wide Guard.
moves.shortDesc: Picks a random move.

moves.name: Trailblaze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1.

abilities.name: Toxic Chain
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's moves have a 30% chance of badly poisoning. This effect comes after a move's inherent secondary effect chance.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's moves have a 30% chance of badly poisoning.

abilities.name: Frisk
abilities.desc: On switch-in, this Pokemon identifies the held items of all opposing Pokemon.
abilities.shortDesc: On switch-in, this Pokemon identifies the held items of all opposing Pokemon.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Choice Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Speed is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Aguav Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Clear Amulet
items.desc: Prevents other Pokemon from lowering the holder's stat stages.

items.name: Weakness Policy
items.desc: If holder is hit super effectively, raises Attack, Sp. Atk by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Lum Berry
items.desc: Holder cures itself if it has a non-volatile status or is confused. Single use.

items.name: Black Sludge
items.desc: Each turn, if holder is a Poison type, restores 1/16 max HP; loses 1/8 if not.

items.name: Rocky Helmet
items.desc: If holder is hit by a contact move, the attacker loses 1/6 of its max HP.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Lansat Berry
items.desc: Holder gains the Focus Energy effect when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Eject Pack
items.desc: If the holder's stat stages are lowered, it switches to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Expert Belt
items.desc: Holder's attacks that are super effective against the target do 1.2x damage.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: King's Rock
items.desc: Holder's attacks without a chance to make the target flinch gain a 10% chance to make the target flinch. Evolves Poliwhirl into Politoed and Slowpoke into Slowking when traded.

items.name: Razor Fang
items.desc: Holder's attacks without a chance to make the target flinch gain a 10% chance to make the target flinch. Evolves Gligar into Gliscor when held and leveled up during the night.

items.name: Bright Powder
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks against the holder is 0.9x.

items.name: Poison Barb
items.desc: Holder's Poison-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Reaper Cloth
items.desc: Evolves Dusclops into Dusknoir when traded.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: Wise Glasses
items.desc: Holder's special attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Toxic Plate
items.desc: Holder's Poison-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Poison type.

items.name: Toxic Orb
items.desc: At the end of every turn, this item attempts to badly poison the holder.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Blunder Policy
items.desc: If the holder misses due to accuracy, its Speed is raised by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Protective Pads
items.desc: Holder's moves are protected from adverse contact effects, except Pickpocket.

items.name: Choice Band
items.desc: Holder's Attack is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Muscle Band
items.desc: Holder's physical attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Mago Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Spe Nature. Single use.

items.name: Adrenaline Orb
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage if it gets affected by Intimidate. Single use.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Ring Target
items.desc: The holder's type immunities granted solely by its typing are negated.

items.name: Room Service
items.desc: If Trick Room is active, the holder's Speed is lowered by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Mirror Herb
items.desc: When an opposing Pokemon raises a stat stage, the holder copies it. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Normal Gem
items.desc: Holder's first successful Normal-type attack will have 1.3x power. Single use.

items.name: Throat Spray
items.desc: Raises holder's Special Attack by 1 stage after it uses a sound move. Single use.

items.name: Fist Plate
items.desc: Holder's Fighting-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Fighting type.

items.name: Light Clay
items.desc: Holder's use of Aurora Veil, Light Screen, or Reflect lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Scope Lens
items.desc: Holder's critical hit ratio is raised by 1 stage.

items.name: Psychic Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Psychic Terrain, raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Petaya Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Sp. Atk by 1 stage when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Razor Claw
items.desc: Holder's critical hit ratio is raised by 1 stage. Evolves Sneasel into Weavile when held and leveled up during the night.

items.name: Light Ball
items.desc: If held by a Pikachu, its Attack and Sp. Atk are doubled.

items.name: Lagging Tail
items.desc: Holder moves last in its priority bracket.

items.name: Kasib Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Ghost-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Power Belt
items.desc: Holder's Speed is halved. The Klutz Ability does not ignore this effect.

items.name: Colbur Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Dark-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Twisted Spoon
items.desc: Holder's Psychic-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Power Herb
items.desc: Holder's two-turn moves complete in one turn (except Sky Drop). Single use.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Big Nugget
items.desc: A big nugget of pure gold that gives off a lustrous gleam.

items.name: Shuca Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Ground-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Custap Berry
items.desc: Holder moves first in its priority bracket when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.
